title: The chip stocks are gearing up for a make-or-break moment this week: Trader
text: The chip stocks are gearing up for a make-or-break moment this week: Trader Nia Warfield Reblog The once-hot chip stocks have sunk from the highs, and one trader says it's a make-or-break week for the group as Nvidia gets ready to report earnings. According to Nathan, mixed earnings from the group's top holdings, Intel INTC and Taiwan Semiconductor 2330-TW , now have the SMH "sitting on key support" around the $100 level. "When you think about those two, Intel and Taiwan [Semiconductor], they went two very different ways right after their earnings," Nathan said.
